<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="J" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Jaw" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Jaw,</orth> the mouth of a beast (Germ. <emph>Rachen</emph>): <cit><quote>he keeps them, like an ape, in the corner of his j.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 4.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 2, 20</bibl></cit>. Plur. <emph>--s,</emph> in the same sense: <bibl n="shak. son 19.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 19, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.148" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 148</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.394" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 394</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 13</bibl>.

